Single-Host Service Orchestratio
This stage evolves the application from manually managed standalone containers to a declarative, service-based deployment model using Docker Compose.
Unlike the standalone approach, Compose defines infrastructure as code.

Services Defined

--> MongoDB
--> MySQL
--> Node.js API
--> Java API
--> Angular Client
--> NGINX Reverse Proxy

All services run on a single Docker host but are defined in a single docker-compose.yml.

